The world is witnessing an upsurge in frigates. Will China fall behind if it does not build this type of warship?
As the major naval powers in the world have recently announced the construction plans of new frigates, it seems that overnight frigates have become the focus of the navies of major powers. First, Japan decided to purchase two new frigates in its 2018 defense budget, making Japan The DEX frigate program finally made a substantial breakthrough, and then Lockheed Martin of the United States recently announced the latest plan for the U.S. FFG frigate program. So where should China&#39;s new frigates go?
With the launch of the latest Type 054A frigate at the end of 2017, it means that as many as 29 Type 054A frigates have been built, approaching the total number of 053H series frigates. Since the first Type 054A was launched in 2006, the construction of 054A has The process has lasted 12 years. Even in the world, except for China, only the &quot;Perry&quot; class frigates built by the United States in the 1970s and 1980s can build such a large number of high-performance general-purpose frigates. Comparable.
The reason why so many 054As are built is also very simple, that is, they are affordable, easy to use, and can supplement the navy&#39;s debts over the years.
The 054A frigate has been favored by the Chinese Navy for many years due to its high cost performance and good combat effectiveness. Its displacement of about 4,000 tons is equipped with a 76mm main gun, and the 32-unit Haihongqi-16 and Yu-8 anti-submarine missiles are launched together. The vertical launch system, 8 YJ-83s and a Z-9 helicopter. Although it was built in 2006 and the design time is very early, its combat effectiveness is not too bad even today. Looking at it, It can also reach the upper-middle level among frigates in the world.
But after all, this is a ship designed in the early 21st century. Putting aside its weapon configuration, its power system and electronic radar equipment are far behind compared with the current mainstream frigates in the world. The same type of frigates in Europe are already equipped with all-electric propulsion. , small multi-functional phased array radar, and large-size helicopter deck, it is time to develop new models.
So how should China&#39;s new frigates be developed? This is directly related to its future positioning and the strategic policy of our Chinese navy.
The future development of the Chinese Navy will definitely become a blue-water navy, and it will also go to the ocean in the future, with the ability to quickly deploy in areas closely related to China&#39;s vital interests, demonstrate the presence of force, and have strong combat effectiveness to protect China when necessary. If the vital interests in this area are not damaged, it seems that the new Hu Weijiang will definitely develop towards large-scale and ocean-going development.
Let’s look at the positioning of new frigates in the future sequence of the Chinese Navy. The future Chinese Navy should be similar to the U.S. Navy. In addition to the necessary offshore defense ships, other main ships will form aircraft carrier battle groups or amphibious assaults as needed. Ship strike group.
The role of the new frigate in the future aircraft carrier battle group should be to serve as the main anti-submarine force and positioning for air clearance in the mid-to-near area. In the amphibious assault ship strike group, it should serve as a frigate. Therefore, according to such needs, the new frigate must be powerful. Anti-submarine capability and good mid-range area release capability.
Based on the above positioning, we can boldly imagine what the future domestic frigates will look like.
First of all, the displacement will be significantly increased compared to the current Type 054A frigate. It is estimated that the displacement of the new frigate will reach about 5,000-6,000 tons; the power system will use a comprehensive QC280 improved gas turbine and two diesel engines. With the electric propulsion system, the maximum speed is expected to reach about 30 knots, and the endurance will also be greatly increased; as for the weapon configuration, the 76mm main gun and 1130 close-in defense gun should be retained, but a Hongqi 10 launch system will be added, and there should be a red flag behind the main gun. A 32-48 unit Hongqi 16 improved vertical launch system that is co-mounted with the Yu-8, and a large 8-16 unit vertical launch system should be installed in the middle and rear of the ship for launching YJ-18 and new cruise missiles; The hangar and parking platform will also be enlarged to accommodate the parking and storage of two 10-ton helicopters; as for the electronic radar system, if it is a high-end configuration, it should be equipped with a small four-sided fixed phased array radar based on the development of 346A. If it is a low-end configuration, it can be used Similar to the multifunctional rotating phased array radar on European frigates.
In this way, the overall level of the new frigate will reach the current first-class level in the world, even if it is compared with the American FFG.
Of course, the above concepts are just the author&#39;s conjectures about the new domestically produced frigates. We can only find out the details when the new frigates are launched. Let us look forward to it together.
